      'backend/src/modules/vehicle-intelligence/trips/decision/trip-decision.engine.ts вАФ splitTripAtGap l√§uft vollst√§ndig in prisma.$transaction: (1) tx.vehicleTrip.update der urspr√Љnglichen Zeile setzt tripStatus=COMPLETED, endTime=params.firstEndAt, endDetectionMode=MID_TRIP_GAP_SPLIT, endConfidence=MEDIUM, durationMinutes=firstDurationMs/60_000, distanceKm=firstEndDistanceKm ?? originalTrip.distanceKm, qualityStatus=VERIFIED, behaviorSummaryStatus=PENDING, drivingImpactStatus=PENDING, rawDetectionMeta={splitReason, splitTriggeredBy, splitGapMs, splitFirstEndAt, splitSecondStartAt}. (2) tx.vehicleTrip.create f√Љr den secondTrip mit tripStatus=ONGOING, tripSource=V2_LIVE|REPAIRED je nach triggeredBy, startTime=params.secondStartAt, startDetectionMode=MID_TRIP_GAP_SPLIT, isRepaired=(triggeredBy===RECONCILIATION), rawDetectionMeta={splitFrom, splitReason, splitTriggeredBy, splitGapMs}. (3) tx.vehicleTripWaypoint.updateMany({where:{tripId:originalId, recordedAt:{gte:secondStartAt}}, data:{tripId:secondTrip.id}}). Return: {firstTripId, secondTripId, movedWaypoints}. Logger-Line gibt vehicleId, orgId, Trip-IDs, Gap-Dauer und moved-Count aus',
